<br>
Not argueing that it shouldnt be used in public places at all.  I dont, and in case of work or school, you wouldnt even know what I am all about from meeting me there.  I am quite often the most flamboyant outspoken person in many of my classes, but I am a choir girl in school and work compared to real life.  <br>
<br>
In the end, you are completely and totally correct.  Casual word usage shapes the world around us.  Using the word &quot;gay&quot; as a pejorative constantly, and by many people could certainly lead to the decay of homosexuals positive self image.  I can certainly see the damage done.<br>
<br>
My crowd of folks I spend time with are decidely younger however.  And I can guarentee my friends are NOT really affected by it, as they accept it is not meant as an insult.  Then again, I dont hang out with people that are insecure about their identities and thus open to insult from other peoples every day ignorance.  They, like me, deal with what life throws our way.<br>
<br>
Fuck, now I am going to spend the next month carefully watching every word I say.  Guilt is such a bitch.<br>
